Andymark’s Climber in a box uses springs to extend the hook. The reason this is necessary is retraction is done with a rope and winch, and rope is only strong under tension.

Are you aware you can get 6 free springs from Vulcan in the KOP? Is the problem the shipping cost/customs time?

If you are looking for an alternate climber design, I would suggest looking at the Everybot’s climber.

While you do need to use constant force springs for the Climber-in-a-Box (a telescoping arm, technically) you don’t have to use Vulcan springs specifically. McMaster-Carr and other suppliers also carry constant force springs and these are often cheaper than those from Vulcan.
